<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by ejkas:
[B]As a cleric you have 3 main lines of spells
1) First is the Courage line of spells. This is an hp/ac buff, and our most widely used buff. You cannot stack one hp/ac buff with another. In other words you cannot cast daring on someone with valor. In situations where you do attempt to cast a spell from this line on someone with an hp/ac buff 2 things can happen. If your spell is a higher level spell or is the same spell being cast from a higher level, your spell will overwrite the old hp/ac buff. If your spell (as in your situation with drive by buffs) is lower level than that on your target, you will get a message that your spell would not take hold. Don't worry about this... be grateful you don't lose mana anymore when this happens.
Druids have a line of buffs that are also hp/ac, they are the ones that start Skin like _____ (wood, stone, steel, etc). Because of the nature of their buffs, this line of spells will not stack with the cleric courage line. If a higher level druid gives your friend Skin like Nature, you will be unable to cast bravery on him/her.
Our spells in this line are: (lvl)
Courage (1)
Center (9)
Daring (19)
Bravery (24)
Valor (34)
Resolution (44)
Heroism (52)
Fortitude (55)
Aegolism (60)

2) The second line of buffs we receive is a line of Armor class buffs. This is the line starting with Holy Armor. As with hp/ac buffs, ac buffs will not stack with other ac buffs. You cannot cast Spirit armor on a person with Shield of Words. You won't find too much conflict with other classes on this. Rangers are the only class I can think of that might interfere with this. Other buffs, shaman ones in particular, can buff stats that cause an increase in ac; these stack. Your main conflict will come from higher level clerics buffing higher level spells.
Spells in this line: (lvl)
Holy Armor (5)
Spirit Armor (19)
Guard (29)
Armor of Faith (39)
Shield of Words (49)
Bulwark of Faith (57)
Aegis (57)
Aegolism (60)

3) Finally we have our symbol spells. These spells provide an increase in hit points. Symbol spells all require reagents (gems). As with ac buffs, the only conflict you should find is with a higher level cleric buffing your friend.
The symbol spells are: (gem)(lvl)
Symbol of Transal (Cats Eye Agate)(14)
Symbol of Ryltan (Bloodstone)(24)
Symbol of Pinzarn (Jasper)(34)
Symbol of Naltron (Peridot)(44)
Symbol of Marzin (Peridot)(54)
Aegolism (Peridot)(60)

You'll notice I listed Aegolism under all three types of buffs. Aegolism includes the effects of each line of buffs. No hp/ac, ac, or hp spells will stack with Aegolism. Again, the shaman riotous health spells buff stamina causing increased hp, and will stack.

As far as what you can do about it, you have your options. With higher level buffs your tank, and therefore your team, is stronger. I would just start healing earlier if you are worried about the time it take you to heal. You are healing her just as efficiently as before, your spells arent changed. I realize that before you were able to heal 25% of your friends hp in a heal and now only heal 18-19%. This is less than a bubble of health and so seems ineffective. Keep healing or do something else. Your tank can survive longer without your help now, so maybe you have mana to throw in a nuke. If you can kill the mob faster than before, using the same amount of mana as before from healing, then your group has been improved.

If the other buffs really bother you, ask the person not to buff. If they already have, you can ask your friend to click them off (left clicking a beneficial buff removes it) and then cast your own. I don't recommend doing this. Save your mana, kill more, get exp, and then you'll eventually get those buffs that are causing you trouble.


Good Luck,
Ejkas[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
